
[1]unruly

   UNRU'LY, a.

   1. Disregarding restraint; licentious; disposed to violate laws;
   turbulent; ungovernable; as an unruly youth.

   The tongue can no man tame; it is an unruly evil. James. 4.

   2. Accustomed to break over fences and escape from inclosures; apt to
   break or leap fences; as an unruly ox.

   The owner of the unruly ox paid a sum of money, as a civil penalty for
   the ransom of his life.
